Ulaire Enquea    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> *****edit*****<br>
Note to all those who review.  Here is the reason I play Gimli.  He is a champion chump blocker at 2 twilight.  He gives Gandalf another strength +1.  He is not generally out in most games.  He is there in case you have to chuck Greenleaf or Aragorn early because you get a bad draw or some big nasty comes and eats them before you get all your junk out.  I like Gimli&#39;s pump ability in the clinch.  If you like Boromir better you play him.  Also, please do not give me bad reviews because I dont use the Cave Troll.  READ before you say that.  If you still dont believe try it.<br>
*****end edit*****<br>
<br>
For in depth detail of this particular kind of deck refer to my previous posting "Gandalf is Crescent Fresh".  I am only going to hit the highlights here.<br>
<br>
Introduction:<br>
This deck uses the ability to shoot down anything that is a threat combined with the most powerful companion available, to race to site 9.  The shadow side of the deck is swarms created to cycle through your deck to get the cards you need when you need them and kill the opponent if you have to.<br>
<br>
Play choice:<br>
Generally bid low because you never need the liablilty of burdens but you generally want to go first and just stay ahead of them, widening the gap whenever possible.  Abuse Sting and Glamdring and if they dont have anything in hand keep moving.  The only decks I would suggest going second against are Nazgul decks and choke strategy decks.  The only reasons for this are that you dont want the Nazgul sites out, and the  choke deck isnt going to move fast anyways, so get the fellowship cards into hand by dumping stuff on them first turn.  Biggest way to learn a deck like this is to play against everything you can.<br>
<br>
Card choices:<br>
If you have the cards Gandalf is the most efficient at providing a means to destroy any threat coming at you.  Servant of the Secret Fire to reduce minions&#39; power, Stregth of Spirit to allow more aimed archery, or Gimli pump action, and Sleep to clear the board.<br>
<br>
Gandalf&#39;s Cart - The point of this card is that it allows you to cycle your hand more efficiently by dumping cards that will be useful later on.  It can also be pulled by the starting site if you go first.<br>
<br>
Albert Dreary - A sitting condition eliminator.  One of the biggest perks of playing a Gandalf based deck.  Save him for swarms, spies or snows.  Remember he does his thing during the maneuver phase.<br>
<br>
Gimli - Most people disagree with this choice, but if you arent playing against Uruk-Hai he is an excellent chump blocker and he makes Gandalf an additional +1 power.  Doesnt sound like much, but it is huge since the difference between winning and losing a skirmish is often 1 or 2 power.<br>
<br>
Barliman - Another must in any Gandalf deck.  Recycle those awesome spells and dump some early if you have to.  Against some decks 1 sleep might not be enough, but with Barliman you can play it several times.<br>
<br>
Choices for shadow:<br>
There is no cave troll in this deck for a reason.  Please do not tell me this deck is not any good because he isnt in here.  If you decide that he is a must have, by all means put him in YOUR deck.  The guard commander effectively takes his place and I think in many cases he is a better choice.  As I have already described above, this deck is a RACE deck.  For your opponent to beat you he must either kill you (which is VERY difficult) or he must race against you giving you lots of shadow at times.  This deck is a machine for generating shadow AND cycling through your deck.  It can do both well.  The shadow side of this deck can be very effective at killing the fellowship, but if you are facing another Gandalf fellowship, your best bet is to just use the scimitars and They Are Coming to get your fellowship cards and only worry about slowing your opponent down.<br>
<br>
General comments:<br>
-Unless you have looked at your opponents hand and know they have nothing or are just looking to lose the game, never double move into site 5.<br>
-Always drop minions when you can unless you are saving shadow for the next site.  Even if you lose the minions to archery fire, you get to draw that many more cards that could potentially win you the game.  <br>
-Dont put out 5 companions against an Uruk-Hai deck.  Thats just asking for it.  Save your 5th character for when someone dies.  And if you ever have 6 companions out and Enquea beats you down, you deserve it for having 6 companions out.  You heard it here so dont blame me. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=21246"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=21246" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
